textBeforeTable: The RAF Menwith Hill Family Health Clinic provides family practice, pharmacy, immunizations, laboratory, general dentistry, mental health services, family advocacy and public health services in an ambulatory care setting. They provide service to all active duty personnel, as well as, their family members. Space- available appointments are available to retirees and their family members, as well as, civilian DoD employees. The "Right Start" Medical In-Processing briefing is held at 9 a.m. Wednesday mornings in the clinic. This is a mandatory appointment and is highly encouraged for family members. The appointment last approximately two hours. More information can be found at the RAF Menwith Hill clinic factsheet.  The clinic's operating hours are: Menwith Hill Clinic  The Stavanger Medical Aid Station is staffed by one full-time Independent Duty Medical Technician who is the primary care manager for all active duty U.S. military patients.
